July 9 at 10:11 AM ·

Lake Regional Sports Medicine and physicians will provide free sports physicals at Iberia Health Clinic on July 28th 8-5 for high school and middle school athletes.
Students should wear loose fitting clothing and have a parent or guardian present.
Physicals are valid for two years, per MSHAA guidelines.
Face coverings are required. If you do not have a face covering, one will be provided.
Please allow extra time — all participants will be screened for temperature and symptoms, and social distancing guidelines will be followed.

post_text: The Iberia R-V School District has extended its COVID-19 closure through April 24, 2020. Classes are scheduled to resume on April 27, 2020. In the meantime, instruction will continue as currently being implemented, with online and hard-copy systems. Likewise, food deliveries will continue under the method currently being used. Those who have not signed up for food deliveries but wish to use that service may do so by calling school or completing the online form previously published. Changes to these plans will be announced when needed.

shared_text:
Gari Luttrell is with Scott Luttrell.
December 13, 2019 at 10:54 PM ·

Tonight was a WIN for the Iberia Graphic Design Seniors at the 2019 Portfolio Night at Waynesville Career Center!

Congrats Jordan Luttrell for her design being chosen by the Pulaski County Commission as their new logo to be used in all county advertising for years to come.

Congrats to Heather Mote for being chosen Best Overall Showcase.

We have some very talented young ladies. They also designed the event invitation in the first photo.
